This paper deals with sequence classification tasks using a novel approach that integrates attention models and gated recurrent networks. The paper presents results on three different tasks: spoken digit recognition, text-based sentiment analysis, and visual event recognition. These tasks are typically associated with the arXiv CS sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
